                <note rend="inline" type="source">493.11 N 15/215: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-10-04T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 4, 1928—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>335. Following for guidance American Members Joint Commission: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Replying to inquiry from University of Nanking, Department has stated
                            that statements of losses will not be presented to the Joint Commission
                            against the expressed wishes of the claimants, and the Department and
                            its officials in China will, when so advised, treat the statements as
                            having been submitted solely for information purposes.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
